  <steps>
    <step num="0">In a large pot on medium-high heat, gently heat the milk to a simmer. </step>
    <step num="1">Add in the elbow macaroni. Cook until the pasta is tender. </step>
    <step num="2">Once the noodles are cooked, turn off the heat. Add in the butter, cheddar, salt, and pepper. Fold these ingredients with the pasta until the cheese and butter melt into the milk to create a thick sauce. </step>
    <step num="3">Sprinkle with parsley and serve! </step>
    <step num="4">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
